The paper deals with coding theory, specifically the study of double circulant and double negacirculant codes over a semilocal ring. This falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-categories. The paper also involves enumeration and construction of codes, which falls under the discrete mathematics (cs.DM) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of a Gray map, which is a common tool in coding theory and falls under the computer communications (cs.CC) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the parameters and optimality of the constructed codes, which falls under the signal and image processing (cs.SI) sub-category.
